<HEADLINE>
ON-THE-SPOT LARRIMORE PASSES TEST
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CLARENCE E. HILL JR. 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   WICHITA FALLS, Texas _ The player who was under the most
scrutiny Sunday night against the Oakland Raiders made the biggest
impression, Dallas Cowboys coach Dave Campo said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   With Kevin Smith expected to announce his retirement within the
next week, rookie cornerback Kareem Larrimore has moved into the
starting role at left cornerback, becoming the man on the spot.
</P>
<P>
   Campo liked the way Larrimore responded in the game, citing his
go-getter attitude along with his six tackles and pass deflection.
</P>
<P>
   ``He made the biggest jump in the game,'' Campo said. ``He was
one of the guys that stood out. He wanted to be out there. He was
really into the game.''
</P>
<P>
   Campo, however, said one game doesn't make him a starter.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't want him to get the feeling that it is a secure
situation,'' Campo said. ``We still have Charlie (Williams). We
still have Duane Hawthorne. We still have Mario Edwards. There are
still guys who can play that position.''
</P>
<P>
   Conspicuous by his absence on Campo's list of cornerback
possibilities was the player they tabbed on draft day as the heir
apparent to the position, 2000 top draft pick Dwayne Goodrich, who
has been unimpressive so far. Goodrich is sidelined with a strained
hamstring. GUT FEELING POINTS TO SEDER
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys said Tuesday that the statistical battle between
kickers Tim Seder and Rian Lindell was close.
</P>
<P>
   Lindell, who was released Monday, was perfect on three attempts.
Seder was 3-of-4, with his only miss coming on a 58-yard try in the
waning moments of Sunday's 21-20 loss to the Raiders.
</P>
<P>
   Campo said the decision came down to ``a gut feeling.''
</P>
<P>
   ``He is very poised and he handles pressure well,'' Campo said
of Seder.
</P>
<P>
   Campo, however, stressed that while the Seder is now the lone
kicker on the roster, he still must prove that he deserves to be
the team's opening-day kicker.
</P>
<P>
   ``The kicking business is a day-to-day scenario,'' Campo said.
``He knows he will be under scrutiny. This gives him two games to
be prepared for the season.''
</P>
<P>
   Seder, a former high school teacher who is trying to live out a
childhood dream, knows he has a long way to go before Sept. 3.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm just going to continue to work,'' Seder said. ``I can't
let up.'' BRIEFLY
</P>
<P>
   _ The Cowboys waived former TCU linebacker Joe Phipps, who had
been sidelined the past three weeks with a sprained left ankle.
</P>
<P>
   _ Fullback Robert Thomas has a grade one knee sprain. He is
listed as day to day, however it's doubtful that Thomas will be
ready for Saturday's game against the Denver Broncos. In his
absence, the Cowboys will use a lot of two-tight-end sets with
H-back Jackie Harris filling Thomas' fullback role. Ryan Neufeld
will sub for him as a conventional fullback.
</P>
<P>
   _ Running back Emmitt Smith (strained calf) and tight end David
LaFleur (strained groin) could return to practice this week.
However, they might be held out of Saturday's game for
precautionary reasons. Campo said the Cowboys are going to bring
Smith and LaFleur back slowly, because the main focus is for them
to be ready for the Sept. 3 season opener.
</P>
<P>
   _ Guard Larry Allen (fractured hand) guard/tackle Tony Hutson
(knee surgery) and safety Izell Reese (neck surgery) are all
expected to see their first action of the preseason against the
Broncos. All three have been limited in their work in training camp
because of injuries and/or rehab.
</P>
<P>
   _ Defensive end Greg Ellis (leg fracture) and receiver Jason
Tucker (strained groin/toe surgery) won't play against the Broncos,
but are expected to see time in the Cowboys' final preseason game
Aug. 24 against the St. Louis Rams.
</P>
<P>
   _ Dave Campo said the starters will probably play the entire
first half against Broncos, though quarterback Troy Aikman might
split time with Randall Cunningham with the first unit. nn
</P>
</TEXT>
