   NFL PREVIEW BUDGET
</P>
<P>
   PAGE ONE
</P>
<P>
   NFL-PREVIEW _ A look at the state of the NFL heading into the
2000 season. Has expansion watered down the league to the point
where teams such as Atlanta, St. Louis and Tennessee can make it to
the Super Bowl or have the teams at the bottom for so long finally
found the magic to become competitive? Is it a combination of both?
We will attempt to point out three to five major occurrences that
have had a huge impact on the league, including the institution of
the salary cap. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   PAGE TWO
</P>
<P>
   NFL-NFC-CAPSULES _ A team-by-team look at strengths, weaknesses
and personnel changes. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   NFL-NFC-PREVIEW _ Highlights, observations and predictions for
the NFC. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   PAGE THREE
</P>
<P>
   NFL-AFC-CAPSULES _ A team-by-team look at strengths, weaknesses
and personnel changes. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   NFL-AFC-PREVIEW _ Highlights, observations and predictions for
the AFC. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   PAGE FOUR
</P>
<P>
   NFL-RATINGS _ Rating the 31 teams in the NFL from top to bottom.
Power ratings in parentheses, two sentence comment on each team.
With playoff projection at bottom. (Suigiura, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   NFL-PREVIEW _ A preview of NFL season in short takes, including
a look at players worth watching and those who are overrated; key
games of the season and bummer matchups; hottest coaches and
coaches on the hotseat; tributes to great players in possibly their
final year; superstars in the making and players in decline; great
offseason moves and those that weren't so great; reasons to watch
the NFL this year and reasons not to; teams on the rise and those
heading south. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
