<P>
   CVN-YOUNG-VOTERS (Los Angeles) _ The scene was a dark music club
in West Hollywood where heads adorned with nose rings bobbed and
bare midriffs swayed to the free rhythm-and-blues warm-up act. The
headliner, though prepped to talk politics to her young audience,
was no less hip. Blond and willowy like Britney, yet worldly and
savvy at age 27, Karenna Gore Schiff made her way across the stage
at the House of Blues in her latest attempt to tear through the
veil of cynicism shrouding the nation's largest age voting bloc _
young people. By LARA JAKES.
