Gov. George W. Bush were playing defense when they picked their
running mates. Gore's choice of Sen. Joseph Lieberman helps Gore
shield himself from the Republican claim that Bush will restore
``honor and dignity'' to the Oval Office. Bush's pick of Dick
Cheney helps Bush answer skeptics who wonder if Bush has the
``gravitas'' to be president. It's a strange system where one man
can pick the potential next president of the United States. By
HELEN THOMAS.
