<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ On Thursday night, Vice President Al Gore must
walk on to the platform at the Staples Center in Los Angeles and
deliver the speech of his life. Having attained his party's
presidential nomination after two failed attempts, he must now show
that there is genuine substance beneath the exaggerated ardor or
anger he often displays in his public appearance. Success, as he
accepts the Democratic nomination for president, will keep him in
the presidential race with a sporting chance of winning. Failure
could spell the beginning of the end of his political career, at
only 52....By Mary Dejevsky, The Independent &QL;
</P>
