</P>
<P>
   DEM-INTERNET-NYT (Undated) _ If any group was hoping for a
convention ``bounce'' _ the much-vaunted spike in popularity that
supposedly comes from a political convention _ it was the scores of
political Web sites that made their online debut in Los Angeles and
in Philadelphia with lots of gizmos and hype.
</P>
<P>
   But the what the conventions are showing is that the bounce for
these Internet sites is more of, well, a fizzle. While the coming
of the Internet to the conventions was initially heralded as being
as groundbreaking as the advent of convention television 52 years
ago, the reality has been somewhat less impressive _ for the
moment. By Leslie Wayne.
