<P>
   CVN-DEMS-RELIGION (Los Angeles) _ Forty years after John F.
Kennedy came to this city to accept his party's nomination _
pledging allegiance to America and not the Catholic pope _
Democratic leaders are embracing religion with chutzpah. Sen.
Joseph Lieberman's presence on the Democratic ticket _ along with
his Orthodox Jewish _ show the public's growing maturity, observers
say, about God and politics. By Robert Salladay.
</P>
<P>
   CVN-INTERN (Los Angeles) _ When Rendi Norwood ran for student
body president at Texas High in Texarkana, she displayed a bit more
political savvy than most teen-agers. Of course, it didn't hurt
that her mother, Molly Beth Malcolm, is the chairwoman of the Texas
Democratic Party. Now a 20-year-old government and sociology major
at the University of Texas at Austin, Norwood helped with President
Clinton's visit to Los Angeles after a summer stint as a White
House intern. By Peggy Fikac.
</P>
