<P>
   &QR;  ``The Cider House Rules'' (PG-13) _ John Irving adapted his
own novel, so he made the rules. In the first, better half, Dr.
Larch (Michael Caine) delivers babies and performs illegal
abortions in his remote Maine orphanage. In the second,
less-engaging half, Larch's protege, parentless Homer Wells (Tobey
Maguire), runs off with a World War II pilot (Paul Rudd) and his
girlfriend (Charlize Theron) to learn about the world. An uneven
but heartfelt and engaging film with excellent performances by
Caine (who won a supporting actor Oscar) and by Delroy Lindo as a
deceptively charming apple picker. Grade: B
</P>
<P>
   _Eleanor Ringel Gillespie
</P>
