takes a job manning the roulette table at a London casino, looking
for material for a novel. In this twisty, compelling modern film
noir, we get a view of a world where everyone is on the make. And
if they're not, they're patsies. It's a fascinating, hard-edged
portrait of a man who swears he doesn't gamble. The joke is, he
seemed tohem from the wedding party, and disposable). You'll laugh,
