<P>
   SALZBURG-MUSIC (Salzburg, Austria) _ The Finnish composer Kaija
Saariaho had never considered writing an opera until 1992, when she
attended the production by the director Peter Sellars of Messiaen's
``St. Francois d'Assise'' here at the Salzburg Festival. On Tuesday
night the Salzburg Festival presented the world premiere of her
``L'Amour de Loin,'' with a libretto in French by the Lebanese-born
novelist and essayist Amin Maalouf, who, like Saariaho, lives in
France. By Anthony Tommasini.
