<SLUG> BC-MOMMYWILL-RESOLUTIONS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THE `MOMMY WILL' TOP 10
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
 By CATHERINE NEWTON 
 c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Ooooooo, this new school year came fast. Hardly have we finished
gluing collages, practicing our spelling and cleaning out the
debris in the backpacks (so that's where all the Easter candy
went!), when we're at it again: overparenting our kids through
another year.
</P>
<P>
   But with a new year comes a chance for a fresh start, a clean
slate, if you will. An opportunity to walk away from our parenting
bank of bad habits and start drawing on some more substantial moral
matter.
</P>
<P>
   Here are new school-year resolutions, for us, for you, for all
moms who, no matter what we do for or to our children, always do it
in the name of love.
</P>
<P>
   1. I will make sure my child gets enough sleep. (Even if she
cries, whines and whimpers, and tells me I'm the meanest mom in the
world.)
</P>
<P>
   2. I will get my child to school on time. (Even if I'm still
wearing my pajamas when we get there.)
</P>
<P>
   3. I will eat breakfast OR dinner at a table with my family at
least once a day, with no TVs, no books, no spelling words.
</P>
<P>
   4. I will not rescue my child by bringing the homework he has
forgotten. For the third day in a row.
</P>
<P>
   5. I will not threaten the other kid, the ``bad kid,'' but will
let my child fight her own battles, as long as she is not truly in
danger.
</P>
<P>
   6. I will believe: My child's homework is MY CHILD'S homework. I
will believe: She can do it on her own.
</P>
<P>
   7. I will not be annoyed by the room mother who calls me at the
last minute and wants 24 cupcakes for tomorrow. In fact, I will be
the room mother _ or her assistant, because even though I don't
have the time, I realize no one else does either.
</P>
<P>
   8. I will go on one field trip with the class, or lead one Fun
Friday activity, or volunteer to read each week, or somehow help my
child's teacher, because she is my ally and she must remain strong.
</P>
<P>
   9. I will really know my child's friends.
</P>
<P>
   10. I will not say ``Not now'' to my child without thinking
first: ``Why not now?''
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
