<P>
   DEM-RDP-NYT (Los Angeles) _ A roundup: Vice president Al Gore
arrives in Los Angeles for his presidential nomination at the
Democratic National Convention and tells a flag-waving crowd of
supporters that he is leading a ``new guard'' determined to bring
``positive change'' to the country. The Democratic Party plans to
celebrate the selection of Sen. Joseph Lieberman as Al Gore's
vice-presidential running mate, while assuring the party's diverse
constituencies that despite a platform aimed at the center to draw
voters from outside the Democratic fold, the party will not ignore
the concerns of more liberal Democrats.
</P>
<P>
   (EDS: An early version of the roundup by Christopher S. Wren has
moved and will be updated after 9 p.m. ET with a final version
written by Richard L. Berke, with quotes from late speeches.)
