r s BC-GLF-NICKLAUSMOTHER-08     08-16 0144
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GLF-NICKLAUSMOTHER-0817-COX </SLUG>

<TEXT>
<P>
   Nicklaus LOUISVILLE, Ky. - Jack Nicklaus said his mother, Ellen,
90, who died early Wednesday after a two-year illness, would have
wanted it this way. From all indications, she made him promise not
to let her expected death change his plans.
</P>
<P>
   The 60-year-old Nicklaus, playing in what could be his last PGA
Championship, said he will remain in the tournament, which begins
today at Valhalla Golf Club. He is paired with Tiger Woods and
Vijay Singh.
</P>
<P>
   Nicklaus visited his mother in Columbus, Ohio, on Monday. He
found out about her death while on the fourth hole of his practice
round.
</P>
<P>
   ``He will play in the golf tournament, and, by doing so, he is
honoring her wishes to do so,'' said Jim Awtrey, CEO of the PGA of
America.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
