<P>
   INTERNATIONALRUSSIA-SUB _ LONDON _ A British rescue team is
expected to begin a long voyage Thursday to assist a stranded
Russian submarine amid fears that they may arrive too late to save
the lives of 118 crewmembers trapped in the vessel. A flurry of
activity Wednesday _ including a reluctant call by Russian
officials for foreign assistance _ came after the only sign of life
from the submarine fell silent. For days Russian officials have
reported hearing tapping against the Kursk's hull, but the sounds
ceased Wednesday, suggesting the worst for the crew aboard the
submarine about 350 feet below the surface of the Barents Sea.
(Roughton, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Expected to move by 6 p.m. EDT on the NYT wire.
</P>
<P>
   BRITAIN-CONCORDE _ LONDON _ The British and French governments
Wednesday revoked the flight certificates of all 12 remaining
Concordes of British Airways and Air France, effectively putting
the future of the sleek, supersonic jets in question. The drastic
move comes three weeks after the fatal crash of an Air France
Concorde crash outside Paris that killed 113 people. Developing.
(Roughton, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Expected to move by 5 p.m. EDT on the NYT wire.
