   FBN-FALCONS-CLARIDGE _ FLOWERY BRANCH, Ga. _ It didn't take No.
1 pick Travis Claridge long to earn his keep. He has enjoyed some
serious playing time on the offensive line since the exhibition
season began and he's turning heads with his play. (Winkeljohn,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 13.
</P>
<P>
   COWBOYS-KICKER _ Tim Ceder will be the opening-day place-kicker
for the Dallas Cowboys. Ceder was a high school teacher and coach
last year in Ohio, thinking he had no chance of playing in the NFL
someday. Steve Hoffman, the kickers coach, got a tape of Ceder when
he played in college at Ashland University in Ashland, Ohio, liked
his form, and invited him to a tryout. Four months later, he is the
Cowboys' first-team kicker. (Cantu, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
