</P>
<P>
   French's eyes blinked, radiating a panic that seemed more real
than pretend.
</P>
<P>
   They paused. ``Are you OK?'' Mercer asked. French nodded. ``It
was a good fight,'' he said. Their director drew closer. ``You guys
are awesome,'' she said. ``This is a n ``Hot 'N' Throbbing.'' Red
lights pulse when Charlene is writing her saucy screenplays or a
scene from her imagination is being played out. White lights signal
reality, which will crowd the audience in the close 80-seat space
at PushPush Theater.
</P>
<P>
   Vogel's play is hardly the first to take on a social issue:
