<SLUG> BC-FILM-KINGSOFCOMEDY-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LONG LIVE THE KINGS
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
 By MIKI TURNER 
 c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Three years ago when a publicist offered me passes to see a live
comedy tour called ``The Kings of Comedy,'' I didn't hesitate
before declining.
</P>
<P>
   A night watching Steve Harvey and three other little-known
comedians hardly seemed worth putting more miles on the old Honda.
However, had I known then what I know after having seen the film
version of that successful tour, I would have rented a car. The
Kings rule.
</P>
<P>
   Filmed in two nights at the Charlotte Coliseum in Charlotte,
N.C., and directed by Spike Lee, ``The Original Kings of Comedy''
is one of those side-splitting laugh fests. Harvey and Cedric the
Entertainer ``(The Steve Harvey Show),'' D.L. Hughley ``(The
Hughleys)'' and Bernie Mac ``(Life, Get on the Bus)'' are
inventive, raunchy, brilliant, savvy, intoxicating and politically
incorrect comics whose humor not only cracks you up, but also
challenges the way you think.
</P>
<P>
   Their natural tendency toward profanity aside, the comedians'
most valuable asset is their ability to come at you with common
sense, every-man-woman-and-child-over-13 comedy.
</P>
<P>
   Walter Latham, who co-produced the film with David Gale, is the
guiding force behind the Kings of Comedy tour that launched in
summer 1997. Although it seemed like a fairly risky idea _ none of
the comics had much crossover appeal or name recognition _ The
Kings routinely sold out arenas nationwide and grossed $37 million
over the next two years.
</P>
<P>
   ``Kings'' might not exactly make household names of its four
headliners, but it's likely to appeal to mass audiences in much the
same way Richard Pryor's classic ``Live on the Sunset Strip'' and
Eddie Murphy's ``Raw'' did during the '80s. Individually, these
Kings do not possess Pryor's comedic genius or Murphy's broad
appeal, but collectively, they come close.
</P>
<P>
   Lee, in his first big-screen documentary, does a good job of
interweaving live action with backstage hijinks. We see Harvey
conspiring with his handlers to embarrass an audience member in a
front-row hot seat; there's Mac praying with his wife before he
goes on stage; Cedric agonizing over which hat to wear with which
outfit; and Hughley cracking up the others during a poker game.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Original Kings of Comedy'' is rated R for lots of strong
language and adult subject matter. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FILM: ``The Original Kings of Comedy'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   SCORE: 4 1/2 on a 1-5 scale &QL;
</P>
<P>
   STARS: Steve Harvey, Cedric the Entertainer, D.L. Hughley and
Bernie Mac &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DIRECTOR: Spike Lee &QL;
</P>
<P>
   LENGTH: 146 min. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   RATED: R &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
.MDBU/.MDNM/ nn
</P>
</TEXT>
