pro bono work so sharply that they fall far below professional
guidelines for representing people who cannot afford to pay. Vera
Kennedy, 55, and her neighbors are frustrated by the lack of free
legal representation in their community. Kennedy's apartment is
among about 270 households in Hunter's View, a San Francisco public
