<HEADLINE>
NORTHRIDGE SEEKING PRIMARY SECONDARY PLAYERS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JILL PAINTER  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Cal State Northridge secondary coach Junior
Thurman doesn't have a depth chart. He doesn't want one, either.
Not until after Saturday's scrimmage, anyway.
</P>
<P>
   You can hardly blame him.
</P>
<P>
   The first-year CSUN assistant has no returning starters. Bryson
Atkins suffered a season-ending knee injury over the summer, and
Hassan Abdul-Malik, who played in the spring, transferred to Valley
College.
</P>
<P>
   Thurman still is teaching coverages to the newcomers.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're keeping it pretty simple,'' Thurman said. ``(Wednesday)
morning we just put in our fourth coverage. We're taking it slow
because we want to see them play football. We don't want them
thinking too much.''
</P>
<P>
   Karalus Doyle and Cory Oggs have played for the Matadors. Shawn
Watson participated in spring practice, and Sean Atkins transferred
from Sacramento State. Rookie Steve Paysinger and junior college
transfer Martin Bacon are vying for playing time.
</P>
<P>
   ``Mainly with the new guys, there's a lot of learning,'' said
Thurman, whose brother, Dennis, is USC's secondary coach. ``We have
to cut down on the mental mistakes. Everybody has the physical
ability or they wouldn't be here.''
</P>
<P>
   Auburn on CSUN's mind: CSUN is in the process of finding a
Division I-A school to play next season. Auburn is interested.
</P>
<P>
   ``The one guy (athletic director David Housel) that's called
back so far is Auburn,'' Kearin said. ``We're trying to find that
Division I-A game that's vital to our program's budget. ... The
games are great for our program. You get great exposure for the
school and it's a great experience for the kids.''
</P>
<P>
   Ryerson injured: Backup quarterback Mitch Ryerson didn't
practice Tuesday or Wednesday because of a strained calf muscle.
Ryerson said he expects to practice today - the team's first day in
full pads.
</P>
</TEXT>
