Wednesday, August 9 about the role of computers in architecture
misidentified the architectural firm that created an animated film
illustrating the concept for a new General Motors building. The
film was created by Kaplan McLaughlin Diaz of San Francisco and
overseen by one of the firm's project directors, Mark Miller. (It
was later that Miller established a firm, Miller, Kelly Architects
of San Francisco.)
