<SLUG> BC-FBC-USCNOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
OFFENSE WINS THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   COSTA MESA, Calif. _ Depending on your point of view, USC's
scrimmage at Orange Coast College on Wednesday was either a sign of
encouragement or cause f or alarm.
</P>
<P>
   The Trojans' running game certainly took a step forward, as
tailback Sul tan McCullough rushed for 154 yards in 21 carries and
scored two touchdo wns. But those stats also raise alarms about how
USC's defense will stop Penn State's running game in the
season-opener Aug. 27. Remember, the d efense is supposed to be
USC's strength.
</P>
<P>
   It certainly gave USC coach Paul Hackett a reason for pause,
after his l ongest scrimmage ever (3{ hours, 126 plays). With the
team assembled for a post-game talk, Hackett screamed about how
``conditioning'' and `` running the ball'' would determine the
winner in the Kickoff Classic.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think this game will be about the running game,'' Hackett
said. ``It 's a tribute to the offense what they did today, but the
defense has to stop the run.''
</P>
<P>
   True freshman Chris Howard had 82 yards in eight carries,
including a 67 -yard touchdown run to end the scrimmage. Tailback
Malaefou MacKenzie la sted just one play, cutting his hand on a
helmet and needed stitches. He is expected to be OK.
</P>
<P>
   Tight end Antoine Harris re-injured his hamstring, and Hackett
said he w ould only be a part-time player for the Kickoff Classic,
with either Ale x Holmes of Harvard-Westlake or Doyal Butler
replacing him.
</P>
<P>
   The play of the day came from wide receiver Kareem Kelly (two
receptions , 76 yards), who caught an 18-yard touchdown pass from
Carson Palmer (11 -18, 128 yards, one touchdown, one intt2jCPtion)
by tippingwagll ove r cornerback Darrell Rideaux, and then catching
it in mid-air.
</P>
<P>
   Junior David Newbury made three of four field goals is expected
to be an nounced as the starting placekicker today.
</P>
<P>
   Position changes: Linebackers John Cousins and A.J. Single h ave
been moved to defensive end. As previously reported, freshman
defens ive end Malcolm Wooldridge (6-2, 280) arrived Tuesday night
and officially joined the team.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
